{0 Inlay hints (reference counts)}

Show the number of inbound references (backlinks) next to headings and
link targets as inlay hints, giving the user an at-a-glance sense of
how connected a section is.

{1 Activation}

The server advertises [inlayHintProvider] in its capabilities.  The
client requests hints via [textDocument/inlayHint] for a visible range.

{1 Hint placement}

{2 Headings}

For each heading in the requested range, emit an inlay hint {e after}
the heading text showing the count of links across the vault that target
this heading (path + fragment match).

Example rendering: [{v # Introduction  3 refs v}]

{2 Top of file}

A single inlay hint at line 0, character 0 shows the total number of
links that target the file (path-only match, ignoring fragment).

Example rendering: [{v 12 refs v}]

{1 Count computation}

Counts are derived from the vault index — the same resolution used by
{!page-"feature-find-references"}.

{ul
  {- {b File-level count}: number of links across all indexed documents
     that resolve to this file (with or without fragment).}
  {- {b Heading-level count}: number of links whose resolved path
     matches this file {e and} whose fragment matches this heading
     slug.}
}

A count of 0 produces no hint (avoid visual noise).

{1 Hint shape}

{t
  | Field      | Value                                      |
  |------------|--------------------------------------------|
  | position   | end of heading text / start of file        |
  | label      | ["{n} refs"] or ["{n} ref"] when n = 1     |
  | kind       | [InlayHintKind.Parameter]                  |
  | paddingLeft | [true]                                    |
}

{1 Edge cases}

{ul
  {- {b No references}: no hint emitted.}
  {- {b Self-references}: a document linking to its own heading
     counts toward that heading's total.}
  {- {b Embed links} ([![[note]]]): counted as references.}
}
